# candor effect policy for tb-tui-common.
#
# This is a SHARED TUI library — it must stay reusable across more than one app, which means it must
# never reach an APP-COUPLING effect: the network, a database, a subprocess, or IPC. (Those belong in
# the app, or are injected via a trait/callback.) Filesystem + clock are allowed — they're legitimate
# util helpers here (`util::write_atomic`).
#
# Enforced in CI by ci/candor-check.sh using the stable scanner (`cargo install candor-scan`), so no
# nightly toolchain is needed. This same rule is also readable by the full nightly candor lint via
# `cargo candor policy` (AS-EFF-006) if you have it installed.

deny Net Db Exec Ipc
